        <h3>Beyond Basic Translation Skills</h3>
        <p>The role of an AVT professional goes far beyond mastering grammar and vocabulary. They must be well-versed in idioms, specialized terminology, and the nuances of language. This is particularly important in translating films and TV series, where elements like sarcasm, humor, and even offensive language must be rendered skillfully and authentically.</p>
